  "body": "The it's currently implemented, is that every unread message adds to the \"count\" of a badge that's attached to the channel item (as of #2745, it's an `@` symbol in `master` before  https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/commit/b352341295549ec187fbc5cb3ec089525f0fd373).\r\n\r\nThe same logic has been applied in #2745 (https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/commit/b352341295549ec187fbc5cb3ec089525f0fd373) but this needs to be updated.\r\n\r\nThe correct behaviour is that `hasUnreadMessages` is used to indicate any number of unread messages, while the badge is used for rendering the count of mentions in a channel.",
